    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi, \n\nUnfortunately this is not top priority on our list, both for lack of manpower, \nand because we have few user that would give us feedback. \n\nStill the UI of notebook is quite customisable. If you heard of cell toolbar, you \nwill see that with the following snippet in your custom.js you can have a small workaround:\n\n```\n$([IPython.events]).on('app_initialized.NotebookApp', function(){\n    // add here logic that shoudl be run once per **page load**    \n\n    var edit =  function(div, cell) {\n        var button_container = $(div)\n        var button = $('<div/>').addClass('btn btn-mini').text('edit')\n        button.click(function(){ \n             cell.edit() \n        })\n        button_container.append(button);\n    }\n\n    IPython.CellToolbar.register_callback('android.edit', edit);\n    IPython.CellToolbar.register_preset('android', ['android.edit'])\n});\n```\n\n(i've selected \"android\" celltoolbar) \n![capture decran 2013-10-22 a 14 14 40](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/335567/1380859/1cdd6db0-3b13-11e3-8d92-4b26625a5f3d.png)\n\nI'll let you extend to add buttons like run-cell, cut/copy/past .. etc.\nAsk if you need help.\n\nMarking as wishlist.\n\nThanks.\n"
