    "body": "Hi Matthias, thanks for your reply.\n\nI can understand if this is low priority, and I can't complain as it's not as if I'm paying or contributing anything towards the project...!\n\nI am having trouble getting your workaround to work however. I can't seem to find the place I need to put this code. Googling has shown a number of potential places for the custom.js file (which does not exist in my install), including profile_name/static/js/, profile_name/static/custom, and in profile_name/ itself.\n\nAlso, many of the webpages refer to the profiles being found in ~/.ipython, whereas mine is found in .config/ipython.\n\nMaybe it's the case that I'm not running the developer version of iPython Notebook? I don't want to install this unless this is a requirement however.\n\nAny help greatly appreciated.\n"
