    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The background is that it used to be `.ipython` everywhere, but someone complained that we weren't following XDG standards, so on Linux we now use `.config/ipython` unless `.ipython` already exists. Oh, and if both exist, then we use `.config/ipython` as well.\n\nI'm not wild about this for precisely this reason - it confuses people about where their config files are. In fact, I think I'm going to open an issue to simplify matters.\n"
